| 14 | part def CruiseController | **Yes** | Present in reference model |
| 15 | port setSpeedIn : SetSpeedPort in CruiseController | **No** | Reference model uses events/messages, not ports |
| 16 | port speedIn : SpeedPort in CruiseController | **No** | Reference model uses events/messages, not ports |
| 17 | port throttleOut : ThrottlePort in CruiseController | **No** | Reference model uses events/messages, not ports |
| 18 | part def Engine | **Yes** | Present in reference model |

| 22 | part speedometer : Speedometer in CruiseControlSystem | **No** | Reference model does not define this composite part |
| 23 | part controller : CruiseController in CruiseControlSystem | **No** | Reference model does not define this composite part |
| 24 | part engine : Engine in CruiseControlSystem | **No** | Reference model does not define this composite part |

| 26 | connect speedometer.speedOut to controller.speedIn | **Partial** | Reference model has message from speedometer to controller, but not via ports |
| 27 | connect controller.throttleOut to engine.throttleIn | **Partial** | Reference model has message from controller to engine, but not via ports |

For claims 25-27, the reference model expresses these as messages, not as port connections, but the structural communication is present. If we accept semantic equivalence (ignoring the mechanism), these can be considered **supported**.

### Supported Claims

- 10. part def Driver
- 12. part def Speedometer

- 18. part def Engine
